a.  (Not demonstrated) Click on your toolshelf to store your Protoflux tool
1.  If you did not create your own clock at the Mesh Tutorial station, you can grab one of the sample clocks to use
Note: in Desktop mode, press "2" to equip a Development Tool
2.  Open the Dashboard and select "Inventory"
3.  Select "Resonite Essentials", then "Tools"
4.  Double-click on the Development Tool to spawn a tool
5.  Click on the tool and select "Equip Development Tool" to equip it
6.  Close your Dashboard
Note: in Desktop mode, press CTRL+R to secondary click
7.  Target the second hand on your clock and secondary click
Note: in Desktop mode, press CTRL+T to open the Context Menu
8.  Open your Context Menu and select "Open Inspector"
9.  Click the "object root" icon
10. Swap tools to equip your Protoflux tool.
11. Double-click on the "Second Hand Pivot" slot
12. Grab the title "Rotation" from the "Rotation" entry of the "Second Hand Pivot"
13. Open your Context Menu and select "Drive" to create a "Value Field Drive (floatQ)" node
14. Position this node to the right of the "Axis Angle" node
15. Connect the output of the "Axis Angle" node into the "Rotation" input of the "Value Field Drive" node
16. You will now see that the rotation of your second hand is changing every second.
17. Select the "Protoflux" slot and create a child
18. Rename the child to "Seconds"
Note: in Desktop mode, target any node and press and hold CTRL+R to select all of the nodes
19. Secondary click-and-hold to select all of the Protoflux nodes
20. Grab the name of the "Seconds" slot, open your Context menu, and select "Pack Into"
